so these tables show how a card drops off or increases as budget increases
negative slope means that as the rest of the cards int he deck get more expensive, the card gets used less. positive slope means that as the rest of the cards get more expensive, it gets played more
so for example in the counterspells, mana drain only gets used in more expensive decks, cancel only gets used in more budget decks, while counterspell gets used throughout budget and expensive list
